text=:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild%0a:Essential: {Category.LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild$:essential}%0a:Title: Do not speak Chinese in university lounges%0a:Author: xiranw%0a:Section: B%0a:Completed: 25.04.2021 - 22:32%0a:Status: complete%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a----%0a%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%0a[[#history]]%0a#foxbegin 210504-192209-625470#%0a* [-04.05.2021 - 12:22-] || TA_audrey marked as complete%0a#foxend 210504-192209-625470#%0a[[#historyend]]%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Comments for student'''%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a%0a[[#commentsend]]%0a%0a----%0a----%0a!!%0a%0aSummary: \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aSaid a Duke professor%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aIn early 2019, an email sent by a Duke professor warning students to not speak Chinese in university lounges sparked widespread outrage. In the email, the professor said that she had been approached by two other faculty members who witnessed students speaking Chinese in lounge/study areas and who felt that speaking Chinese in such settings was both impolite and showed the students’ lack of effort to improve their English. The two faculty members also wished to identify those students so that they could “remember them if the students ever interviewed for an internship or asked to work with them for a master’s project”.%0a%0aDenying students academic and professional opportunities simply because and only because they choose to speak in a specific language is a textbook example of linguistic discrimination. And unfortunately, such incidents are not isolated. Speakers of minority languages are often decried as unprofessional and/or incompetent by speakers of the prestigious majority language, despite how the language one speaks in has nothing to do with competence. In a country like the United States with a large immigrant population, such clashes between immigrant languages and English are especially common.%0a%0aSources: https://www.cnn.com/2019/01/28/health/duke-professor-warns-chinese-students-speak-english-trnd/index.html%0a%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a(:GradedBy: TA_audrey:)
